## MCP Server Builder

### Step 1: Install SDK
```bash
npm install @modelcontextprotocol/sdk
```

### Step 2: Create server entry point
```js
// mcp-server.js
const { Server } = require('@modelcontextprotocol/sdk/server/index.js');
const { StdioServerTransport } = require('@modelcontextprotocol/sdk/server/stdio.js');

const server = new Server(
  { name: 'my-server', version: '1.0.0' },
  { capabilities: { tools: {}, resources: {}, prompts: {} } }
);
```

### Step 3: Register tools
```js
server.setRequestHandler(ListToolsRequestSchema, async () => ({
  tools: [
    {
      name: 'search',
      description: 'Search for items',
      inputSchema: {
        type: 'object',
        properties: { query: { type: 'string', description: 'Search query' } },
        required: ['query']
      }
    }
  ]
}));

server.setRequestHandler(CallToolRequestSchema, async (request) => {
  if (request.params.name === 'search') {
    const { query } = request.params.arguments;
    const results = await performSearch(query);
    return { content: [{ type: 'text', text: JSON.stringify(results) }] };
  }
  throw new Error(`Unknown tool: ${request.params.name}`);
});
```

### Step 4: Start with stdio transport
```js
async function main() {
  const transport = new StdioServerTransport();
  await server.connect(transport);
  process.stderr.write('MCP server ready\n');
}
main().catch(console.error);
```

### Step 5: Add HTTP transport (optional)
```js
const { StreamableHTTPServerTransport } = require('@modelcontextprotocol/sdk/server/streamableHttp.js');
const express = require('express');
const app = express();
app.use(express.json());
app.post('/mcp', async (req, res) => {
  const transport = new StreamableHTTPServerTransport({ sessionIdGenerator: undefined });
  await server.connect(transport);
  await transport.handleRequest(req, res, req.body);
});
app.listen(3000);
```

### Claude Desktop config
```json
{
  "mcpServers": {
    "my-server": {
      "command": "node",
      "args": ["/absolute/path/to/mcp-server.js"]
    }
  }
}
```

### Checklist
- [ ] Tools have clear descriptions and typed inputSchema
- [ ] Error handling returns MCP error responses, not thrown exceptions
- [ ] stdio transport for Claude Desktop; HTTP for web clients
- [ ] Server name/version set in constructor
- [ ] Capabilities declared match handlers registered

## Web Artifacts Builder

### Core Principle
Single HTML file. No build step. No dependencies fetched at runtime if possible.
Target: open file → see working interactive demo.

### Structure
```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1">
  <title>Prototype: [Feature Name]</title>
  <style>
    /* All CSS inline — no external sheets */
    :root {
      --accent: #6366f1;
      --surface: #f8fafc;
      --text: #1e293b;
    }
    * { box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0; padding: 0; }
    body { font-family: system-ui, sans-serif; background: var(--surface); color: var(--text); }
  </style>
</head>
<body>
  <!-- Semantic HTML structure -->
  <main id="app"></main>

  <script>
    // Vanilla JS state machine — no framework needed for prototypes
    const state = { items: [], loading: false };

    function render() {
      document.getElementById('app').innerHTML = view(state);
      bindEvents();
    }

    function view(s) {
      return `<section>...</section>`;
    }

    function bindEvents() {
      document.querySelectorAll('[data-action]').forEach(el => {
        el.addEventListener('click', () => dispatch(el.dataset.action, el.dataset));
      });
    }

    function dispatch(action, data) {
      // update state, re-render
      render();
    }

    render();
  </script>
</body>
</html>
```

### When to use
- Stakeholder demos before production build
- Design system component exploration
- Algorithm or interaction proof-of-concept
- Shared via file or GitHub Gist

### What NOT to do in artifacts
- Don't add a build pipeline (webpack, vite)
- Don't import from npm without a CDN fallback
- Don't use framework-specific syntax if vanilla JS suffices

### Checklist
- [ ] Opens in browser without any install step
- [ ] All assets inline or from reliable CDN
- [ ] Mobile viewport meta tag present
- [ ] Key interactions work without console errors
- [ ] Semantic HTML (not div soup)
